The earliest date of data available

Source: R/weathervane.R
earliest_dataset_date.Rd

Return a Date object containing the earliest date of data available from the SILO server. (As of checking on 10/03/2021, the earliest date is 01/01/1889, although this may change.)

Usage

earliest_dataset_date()

Value

A Date object representing the earliest date

Examples

weathervane:::earliest_dataset_date()
#> [1] "1889-01-01"
